name: solomon abner
text: I really enjoyed A Touch of Soul. The service was excellent and the ambiance was mesmerizing and the food could be called a taste of soul,  simply delicious. Jerry aka Mother the owner and founder of this family business makes sure your a part of the family from the moment you enter the door and you are greeted and waited on by her beautiful daughters , granddaughter  and niece. It was a soulful experience!

name: Beverly Green
text: Excellent health rating--better food! Good people, great service. Freshly cooked food every day, these people are on the way up. Help support local Montgomery restaurants. We need to keep places like this with good, fresh food available and open for those of us who work downtown. Five stars

name: Michael P
text: The food was great! Kinda small portions. The wait, though! It took them over an hour to serve our group of 20, and about a third of the orders were wrong! Management has done a great job of honing in on a good menu, but they really need to work on waiting on their customers (getting drinks out quickly) and on order fulfillment quickly.

name: Kristin Byrd
text: I love the Sunday Brunch concept. I went a couple of weeks ago and was pleasantly surprised that they let me order ala carte, so to speak. What I wasn't pleasantly surprised with was my burned bacon. I mean really burnt, lol. I was the last to arrive in our four person party. I ordered water that I never received. My friend, a promoter for the event, brought it to me. *sigh* I think maybe they just need to staff the restaurant better. The young lady that served us was nice and cordial but visibly overwhelmed. I may give it one more chance- the waffle was delicious and the music was awesome :).

name: Kyle Flenar
text: Came with a group after we called in advance. Over half my group ate dinner, dessert, paid, and decided to leave before we got food. No comments letting us know where the food was. I had to get up and stop someone to get water after waiting an hour for it. I got chicken and cornbread and the cornbread was small and chicken was dry and luke warm. Severely disappointed.
